								HAD BETTER
								
								
it is used to give some suggestions to give advice in present or future

						#examples(positive):  sub + had better + v1 

you had better start at once
i had better study everytime
we had better enter the exam hall before 10am or else we will not be allowed 
i had better stay away from this problem
he had better marry her
they had better take the rest
i'd better go now before the traffic gets too bad
she 'd better get here or esle she will miss the opening ceremony


					#usage of had better (negative) sub + had better +not +v1

she had better not mingle with her
i had better not waste time
i had better not misbehave in the class
they had better not miss the chance
you had better not go there



